25/04/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The Serbian police have arrested one more person suspected of helping Bosnian Serb wartime commander Ratko Mladic evade justice. Local media identified the suspect as Ratko Vucetic, 63, a retired Navy captain. Vucetic appeared before a judge on Monday and was ordered remanded in custody. The arrest sparked new speculation in Belgrade media that Mladic might be arrested by the end of the month, as promised. (RTS, Politika, Blic - 25/04/06; Reuters, AP, AFP, Tanjug - 24/04/06)
